<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-281-353  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 281 353.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Journal of Systems Management  Jan 1989 v40 n1 p10(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Managing very large system development efforts.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kuzman, Richard J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Managing a system development effort requires setting up anoverall plan in four fundamental areas: organization, planning,communications and execution.andP;  The program management organizationcan be either a matrix organization, in which resources arelocated across organizational boundaries, or a traditionalorganization.andP;  The program management plan provides an overview,the concept of execution, a financial overview, points of contactsand responsibilities and action plans for individual sections.andO;Communications in a large system development effort are crucial.andO;Two effective methods are publishing a monthly or quarterlynewsletter and having program reviews which all project managersattend.andP;  Execution of the plan involves determining if milestonesare being met, expenditure rates are not overbudget, making surethat nothing has been overlooked and ensuring high-qualitydeliverables.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Project ManagementSystem DevelopmentManagementInformation SystemsInformation Resource ManagementBusiness Planning.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablechart.andO;Caption:   Program management plan. (table)Program management. (chart)Preparing a program management plan (PMP). (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>